creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: scowling hunchback figure with hooked nose, and large brimmed hat facing L; posed with pointy, short epee in each hand
provenance: [Pia Gallo, Chicago; sold 1986, to Andrus]; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
title: Duelist with Two Daggers, From Varie Figure Gobbi
